# [[project_name]] — Flutterator DDD architecture

## lib/ layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `lib/core/` | Shared kernel: model (failures, VOs), infrastructure mixins, `app_widget`, `error_localizer` |
| `lib/domain/<entity>/` | Shared domain: `model/` + `infrastructure/` only — no UI, no BLoC |
| `lib/domain/enums/` | Domain enums |
| `lib/features/<feature>/` | Vertical features: `application/` (BLoC) + `presentation/` (UI) |
| `lib/features/components/` | Reusable UI components with their own BLoC |
| `lib/apis/` | HTTP client, Retrofit services, interceptors |
| `lib/logging/`, `lib/storage/` | Cross-cutting infrastructure |
| `lib/widgets/common/` | App-wide widgets (CustomScaffold, Loading, Error, UnknownState) |

Entry points: `lib/main.dart`, `lib/injection.dart`, `lib/router.dart`.

{% if login %}
With login enabled: `lib/domain/auth/`, `lib/features/auth/`, `lib/features/auth/sign_in_form/`.
{% endif %}

## Layer boundaries

- `domain/` must not import from `features/` or Flutter widgets.
- `features/*/application/` must not import presentation widgets.
- `presentation/` uses repositories via interfaces in `domain/*/model/i_*_repository.dart`.
- Use `@injectable` / `get_it` — do not instantiate repositories in widgets.

## How to add code

Write Dart files manually following `docs/architecture/FILE_TEMPLATES.md` and `docs/architecture/REFERENCE_IMPLEMENTATIONS.md`.

**Never run `flutterator` CLI commands** (`flutterator create`, `flutterator add-*`). Agents implement code directly.

## Epic workflow

Use skill `/epic-delivery` for high-level features. See `docs/epics/README.md`.
